"{\"uid\": \"smh.com.au-world-europe-teen-terror-plot-to-attack-olympics-foiled-by-french-security-services-20240601-p5jiff.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"We are sorry, this feature is currently unavailable.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are working to restore it.\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please try again later.\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was published1yearago  Add articles to your saved list and come back to them any time.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"London:French security services have arrested a teenager suspected of plotting an Islamic State-inspired attack during the Paris Olympic Games, officials said on Friday.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 208, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999982370811346, \"rank\": 9.354829796205404e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An 18-year-old man from Chechnya, who wanted \\\"to die and become a martyr\\\", was said to be targeting the Geoffroy-Guichard Stadium in Saint-\\u00c9tienne, which will hold football matches during the Games to be held from July 26 to August 11.\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chechnya\", \"score\": 0.9999999985921022, \"rank\": 1.407804902390565e-09, \"text\": \"Chechnya\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chechnya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chechnya\"}, {\"begin\": 505, \"end\": 518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6539768094023178e-16, \"text\": \"Saint-\\u00c9tienne\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Police officers patrol the Trocadero plaza near the Eiffel Tower in October 2023.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Security authorities have foiled a plan to attack soccer events during the Paris Olympics.Credit:AP  France is on its highest terror alert level ahead of the Games, when about 10 million visitors and 10,000 athletes are expected.\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 788, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999827746252, \"rank\": 1.7225444715654587e-08, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The events will be held mostly in the capital, but other towns and cities around the country will also host some disciplines as well as individual games.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The domestic intelligence agency, the DGSI, arrested the teen in Saint-\\u00c9tienne, south-west of Lyon, on May 22, authorities said, calling it the \\\"first foiled attack against the Olympic Games\\\".\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Directorate_for_Internal_Security\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"DGSI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Directorate_for_Internal_Security\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Directorate_for_Internal_Security\"}, {\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6539768094023178e-16, \"text\": \"Saint-\\u00c9tienne\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 0.9999999985529939, \"rank\": 1.447140429927255e-09, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Interior Minister Gerald Darmanin said the suspect had \\\"intended to attack spectators\\\" but also security forces to \\\"die and become a martyr\\\", adding that it was the 50th attack foiled by intelligence services since 2017.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 0.9995391798178439, \"rank\": 0.00046103263501902163, \"text\": \"Interior Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"score\": 0.9999895822690313, \"rank\": 1.0379329276949663e-05, \"text\": \"Gerald\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The teenager had been scouting locations, according to a source close to the investigation.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Darmanin said the suspect was arrested at home.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's anti-terror prosecutor's office, PNAT, said the teenager was charged on Sunday with terrorist conspiracy with a view to preparing crimes against a person.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1633, \"end\": 1639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9971654820353713, \"rank\": 0.0028421176831930693, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was subsequently remanded in custody.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Investigations are continuing as part of a judicial inquiry.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the matches due to be held at the stadium in Saint-\\u00c9tienne are France against Canada and the United States versus Guinea.\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1951, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6539768094023178e-16, \"text\": \"Saint-\\u00c9tienne\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Geoffroy-Guichard\"}, {\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9971654820353713, \"rank\": 0.0028421176831930693, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1984, \"end\": 1990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999997457039494, \"rank\": 2.4242337065187366e-07, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7330975156464933, \"rank\": 0.36407500863846504, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Morocco will also take on both Argentina and Ukraine in the city, with Canada playing New Zealand and Germany facing Zambia.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9999814124761913, \"rank\": 1.8466702294345033e-05, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}, {\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina\", \"score\": 0.9998215383816464, \"rank\": 0.00017664672734290802, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina\"}, {\"begin\": 2073, \"end\": 2080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.99999998658177, \"rank\": 9.182314680717676e-09, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999997457039494, \"rank\": 2.4242337065187366e-07, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7239473215747116, \"rank\": 0.17242020087510315, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2130, \"end\": 2137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9888298569288143, \"rank\": 0.011240880063796999, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2145, \"end\": 2151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia\", \"score\": 0.9676495230928455, \"rank\": 0.033431983168140646, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French authorities remain nervous aboutthe security situation, especially since the outbreak of war in Gaza in October, and face persistent questions about the risk of an attack.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2154, \"end\": 2160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999982370811346, \"rank\": 9.354829796205404e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2257, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9971796193452725, \"rank\": 0.002828357700191611, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics have been attacked before.\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1972 in Munich, two members of the Israeli team were killed and nine taken hostage by a Palestinian militant organisation; and in 1996 in Atlanta, a domestic terrorist pipe bombing killed one person and injured 111.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2384, \"end\": 2390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.621995534579729, \"rank\": 0.6058988294739167, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2411, \"end\": 2418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 0.9998094833588734, \"rank\": 0.00015121161323727173, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 2464, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9725181480821885, \"rank\": 0.028207973729124584, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 2514, \"end\": 2521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.391584706482172e-15, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Darmanin said there were multiple potential threats, including those from Islamic extremist groups, violent environmental activists, far-right groups and cyberattacks from Russia or other adversaries.\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2793, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2667, \"end\": 2691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Islamic extremist groups\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_extremism\"}, {\"begin\": 2765, \"end\": 2771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999978381311, \"rank\": 2.1383487055198848e-09, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most concerns have focused on the opening ceremony on July 26, which will take place over a six-kilometre stretch of the River Seine - the first time a Summer Olympics has begun outside an athletics stadium.\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2915, \"end\": 2926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 45,000 officers will police the vast area, and large parts of the city's centre will be out of bounds for everyone except ticket holders and residents.\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France has been repeatedly hit by deadly Islamic State attacks, including the Bataclan theatre massacre in 2015 in which extremists opened fire on concert-goers and held hostages for hours.\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3166, \"end\": 3172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9971654820353713, \"rank\": 0.0028421176831930693, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3207, \"end\": 3220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2742957401822828e-18, \"text\": \"Islamic State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 3207, \"end\": 3220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2742957401822828e-18, \"text\": \"Islamic State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bataclan theatre massacre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/November_2015_Paris_attacks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"InOctober last year, a radicalised 20-year-old Chechen, who had sworn allegiance to IS, killed a teacher in the northern French town of Arras.\", \"from\": 3356, \"to\": 3498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3403, \"end\": 3410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chechnya\", \"score\": 0.9999338785379811, \"rank\": 6.612582099273244e-05, \"text\": \"Chechen\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chechnya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chechnya\"}, {\"begin\": 3477, \"end\": 3488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\", \"score\": 0.999967104937146, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French town\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frenchtown_(ghost_town),_Maryland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris organising committee said in a statement it applauded the efficiency of the law-enforcement services and \\\"their exceptional mobilisation to ensure the security of the Games\\\".\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3504, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.776538034897694e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Security is the No.1 priority for Paris 2024,\\\" it said.\", \"from\": 3686, \"to\": 3742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3721, \"end\": 3731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0875261432533545e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French President Emmanuel Macron said in April the opening ceremony could be moved from the Seine to a different site in the event of a security threat.\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3744, \"end\": 3760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 3761, \"end\": 3776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 3836, \"end\": 3841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999993328358366, \"rank\": 6.671646231859834e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Options include the Trocadero gardens, beneath the Eiffel Tower, or even the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3917, \"end\": 3926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"score\": 0.9982609933229762, \"rank\": 0.001742027500345786, \"text\": \"Trocadero\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\"}, {\"begin\": 3974, \"end\": 3989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic torch relay is under way in France, involving a \\\"security bubble\\\" of 100 officers including anti-drone specialists and anti-terror police.\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3996, \"end\": 4009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5030626836506945e-18, \"text\": \"Olympic torch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}, {\"begin\": 4032, \"end\": 4038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9971654820353713, \"rank\": 0.0028421176831930693, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the first three weeks of the 12,000-kilometre trip, 78 people were arrested for trying to disrupt the relay and 30 suspect drones were intercepted, according to the interior ministry.\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get a note directly from our foreigncorrespondentson what's making headlines around the world.Sign up for the weekly What in the World newsletter here.\", \"from\": 4335, \"to\": 4486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a92025\", \"from\": 4488, \"to\": 4503, \"entities\": []}]}"